00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:18,320
 So what Paul is saying,

220
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:21,520
 actually what's a lot more important than us knowing God

221
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:26,480
 is that we are known by God, that he knows us.

222
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:33,080
 You are known by God, the creator of the universe

223
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:37,360
 who holds everything in his hands, who knows, he knows you.

224
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:40,200
 You are his beloved child.

225
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:45,460
 And again, Paul is trying to take the Galatians

226
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:50,000
 to reminding them of this incredible truth

227
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,080
 about their identity.

228
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,320
 They are known by God.

229
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,680
 They are children of God.

230
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:54,840
 He knows their name.

231
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,960
 He knows what's going on in their lives.

232
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,420
 He knows everything.

233
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:01,280
 That's amazing.

234
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,680
 That's incredible.

235
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,520
 And again, the question is,

236
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,520
 why would you go back to something else?

